article.headline: Morehead St. 70, Austin Peay 66
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- Morehead State senior guard Quentin Pryor scored 20 points to lead the Eagles to a 70-66 win Thursday night over Austin Peay at Johnson Arena. The Eagles built a 20-point first-half lead only to see Austin Peay make a comeback in the second half. Austin Peays Landon Shipley drilled a 3-pointer with 1:29 left to cut the Eagle advantage to 69-66. The Governors had two chances to tie or take the lead but missed field attempts, which set up a Cody Ballard free throw with less than a second to play to seal the win. The win improved Morehead State to 4-3 (1-0 Ohio Valley Conference). The Eagles had only four wins during the 2005-06 season. Pryor finished 8-of-12 from the field, including 3-of-5 from three-point range. Shaun Williams chipped in with 15, hitting 7-of-12 from the floor, and Ballard had 10. Austin Peay (2-4, 1-1 OVC) was topped by Shipleys 14, all coming in the second half. Drake Reed and Derek Wright each finished with 12. The Eagles managed to hit only 6-of-13 from the free throw line while Austin Peay connected on 14-of-18.
